The car maker says more than 7,000 of the vehicles are being recalled over airbag issues and this comes after the Takata Corporation last year declared its air bags defective. JOHANNESBURG - Mitsubishi South Africa has declined to give further details after recalling of thousands of Pajeros built between 2007 and 2016.In an earlier statement, the carmaker says more than 7,000 vehicles are being recalled in this country due to issues around airbags.It s part of a global recall after the Takata Corporation last year declared its air bags defective.At least 11 deaths were reported in the United States linked to airbags that ruptured.Mitsubishi South Africa says it has been receiving enquiries since it released its statement on Thursday afternoon and has nothing more to say to the media.The car maker has advised drivers to follow the instructions on its website for assistance.